headline: TRMB Q2 Deep Dive: Subscription Model and AI Initiatives Support Stable Outlook
summary: Geospatial technology provider Trimble (NASDAQ:TRMB) announced better-than-expected revenue in Q2 CY2025, but sales were flat year on year at $875.7 million. On top of that, next quarter’s revenue guidance ($870 million at the midpoint) was surprisingly good and 3.6% above what analysts were expecting. Its non-GAAP profit of $0.71 per share was 13.6% above analysts’ consensus estimates.
